messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I need police.
What's your emergency?
I know there's an Amber Alert on TV for this little boy.
Okay.
And there is a young man that looks just like the guy they said took the little boy.
Where? Where are you?
He's right here on Eddie Road, right near the underpass.
Eddie and where?
What is this street? I'm at Eddie Road and 131.
Eddie Road and 131?
Yes, Eddie Road.
What does he have on?
He has on a black leather coat. He has a small child with him.
Okay, do not lose visual on this man.
I'm trying to go back. He's standing right here.
Stay on the line.
I really am not sure what to do.
Just keep an eye on him.
He's under the bridge where I said he was.
Okay. Turn back around if you can.
I got him right here.
Can you describe him?
I can't tell. I didn't get a good look.
Does he have on a black leather coat?
Yes. He's approximately five foot six.
Does the child have on a bubble coat?
Yes.
Does the child have on khaki pants?
Yes.
And you are at Eddie and 133rd?
Yes.
Do not leave the area, please.
He's going towards 131st.
Is he running or walking?
He's not running. He's heading up the road.
Be advised the male is now going towards 131st.
He's going up the hill right here at the overpass.
Do you think he noticed you?
Yes. He's not hiding anymore.
What type of vehicle are you in, ma'am?
I'm in a blue Chevy Cobalt.
Exactly where are you now?
I'm sitting in the middle of the street and people are blowing their horns at me.
Okay. Stay safe.
He's right there! Do you see him?
Ma'am?
I'm going to follow him.
What's your name, sweetie?
Jacqueline Harris.
Jacqueline? What's your last name?
Harris.
What's your phone number, Ms. Harris?
Mm-hmm.
Thank you so much, Ms. Harris.
No problem.
